cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.IT 

This paper discusses the application of Software-Defined Networks (SDN) in the future Internet to support end-to-end Quality of Service (QoS) provisioning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the challenges of inter-domain collaboration and resource allocation, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper proposes a network abstraction model and end-to-end resource allocation scheme, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
